cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper involves the use of generative adversarial networks for image-to-image translation with natural language descriptions as guidance. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes novel architectures and loss functions, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the experiments are conducted on the COCO dataset, which is commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research, indicating that this sub-category is also a possibility.
